==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*ἀρχιερεύς / archiereus / ar-khee-er-yuce'
From G746 and G2409; the high priest (literally of the Jews, typically Christ); by extension a chief priest: 

===Noun===
'''ἀρχιερεύς'''

# chief (high) [[priest]], chief of the priests.

